ons & University Archives    Finding Aids    Rare Books    Maps & GIS    Digital Images    Using Special Collections & University Archives    Special Collections Research Guides       Eyebrow menu    Contact Us    My Accounts    Give to the Library    COVID-19    UIC menu    UIC.edu    Campus Map    UIC Today     Toggle Search                  Breadcrumbs    Home    Help     Find health information (non-UIC guests)   The Library of the Health Sciences provides support for individuals outside of the UIC community to access health information.  All LHS locations (Chicago, Peoria and Rockford) are open to the public.        The UIC Libraries of the Health Sciences are proud to be a Partner Outreach Library with the Greater Midwest Region of the National Network of Libraries of Medicine.   Services offered  All locations   Use visitor research computers to search library resources and government websites such as MedlinePlus for health information. Bring a flash drive to save information.  Ask to speak to a librarian or make an appointment for help finding health information (in person M-F, during business hours).   Special exhibits are open to the public. Check the events calendar.   Peoria   Members of the public may open a library account and check out a maximum of 3 books at a time. Bring a state ID to the help desk to open an account.   Rockford   Members of the public may open a library account and check out books. Bring a state ID to the help desk to open an account.   Upcoming community health events   See events at our health sciences libraries.   Additional information   Consumer Health Online Research Guide  MedlinePlus  KidsHealth  How to Evaluate Health Information on the Internet (NIH)       How Do I...?     Visitor services    Use library computers (Chicago campus)    Use library computers (Peoria campus)    Alumni services    Visit Special Collections and University Archives     Get More Help        Filter by Location    Chicago-Daley    Chicago-Health Sc